    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">What's the biggest mistake people make when buying Napa Valley wine?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">The most common mistake is assuming all Napa wines are expensive cult bottles, missing excellent values from established producers like Inglenook, Schramsberg, or Chateau Montelena's lower-tier offerings. Many buyers also focus solely on Cabernet Sauvignon, overlooking Napa's exceptional Chardonnay, Sauvignon Blanc, and even Zinfandel from producers like Turley or Frog's Leap. Research specific vineyards and vintages rather than buying based solely on the Napa Valley name, as quality and value vary significantly across producers.</p>
