    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">When is the best time to visit Napa Valley for wine tasting?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">September through November offers harvest season excitement with crush activities and ideal weather, though expect crowds and higher prices during peak harvest in September. Spring (March-May) provides beautiful vineyard scenery with budbreak and flowering, plus easier reservations and lower accommodation costs. Avoid July and August when temperatures often exceed 90°F, making outdoor tastings uncomfortable, and winter months when many smaller wineries have limited hours or close entirely.</p>
